FBIS3-53430 "drnes010_v_94001" FBIS-NES-94-010 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Jan 1994 Pakistan Leghari, Bhutto Urge Afghanistan Cease-Fire BK1301154894 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 1500 GMT 13 Jan 94 BK1301154894 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network Language: Urdu Article Type:BFN [Text] President Sardar Farooq Ahamd Khan Leghari and Prime Minister Benazir Bhutto have appealed together to the Afghan president, the prime minister, and the leaders of other groups to observe a cease-fire from 0600 [0100 GMT] tomorrow morning so as to help initiate the process of reconciliation and understanding. They said, soon after the observance of the cease-fire, Pakistan will send relief materials, including (?three) hospitals, to Afghanistan on humanitarian grounds.
